                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Fian2 wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Sebilis (and other light blue zones) - Great place to charm.  If your hasted charm pet attacks you, it is not that difficult to mez him and his friend, and recharm before they eat through your rune.
<br />

<br />
BoT - My best experience charming.  On one occasion, both myself and a magician had charmed, snared pets and we tore through the content.  Killing the named mob was so easy and fast.  On other occasions I have been known to charm an unhasted mob to help with dps for a specific fight.
<br />

<br />
LDON Normal - Was way too stressful trying to do cc in Guk along with managing a charmed pet.  The DPS gain was not that useful.
<br />

<br />
LDON Hard - I am not that stupid.  (:
<br />

<br />
Vxed/Tipt - Every single time I have done this, the group has failed.  We manage to kill for a while, but then charm breaks at a bad time or an add attacks us in the back and the group wipes.  
<br />

<br />
PoV - I could charm worms and then run to exit when charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
HoH - Had a lot of problems here (trying to solo or duo)
<br />

<br />
Tactics - Had one successful group that included 2 enchanters (one charmed mob) 1 cleric and 1 druid.  Attempts to solo charm here were not pretty.
<br />

<br />
Based on this, if they think that charm is too much power, I would recommend reducing dps if the mob is snared.  Beyond that, the fear of charm breaks would prevent most enchanters from even considering an attempt to charm something that is a 1k+ hitter.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
seb - solo its different, but in your 50's I had plenty of cc to do. A charmed pet just wasn't helpful at that time.
<br />

<br />
bot - If you're just starting out, try deep south with a snarer. Dont charm giants, stick to the elementals. 
<br />

<br />
ldon - Charm as soon as possible. These become trivial almost as soon as you ding 65. 
<br />

<br />
ldon hard - charm can be the difference between win and lose here. I'm not a ldon fan though.
<br />

<br />
vxed and tipt - Tipt especially was the first time EQ had my blood racing in a long time. When you get it right this is the business.
<br />

<br />
pov - Head to the north east corner, there's a nice space to kite on break, both sides of castle are fine too if ne is taken. Inner cave is doable, but generally you don't want to be close to your pet, especially if like me you have low hp.
<br />

<br />
hoh - Built for enchanters. I solo here alot and duo or trio when ever a guildie is lfg. If you duo or more, you have to drive the group.
<br />

<br />
tactics - Great zone. really time to strut your stuff. The pit will test you until you get it down, and keeping a giant pet is brilliant if you want to head further in with a group.
<br />

<br />
If you're on VS I'll happily show you around HoH, Everything you learn there is directly applicable to every other zone you mentioned.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
