                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Sebilis (and other light blue zones) - I did a lot of charm soloing in Nurga and low-end Droga to raise Chardok faction.  It was trivial with Arcane Rune and Eldritch Rune.
<br />

<br />
BoT/HoH - I haven't done much charming here and no charm soloing.  The groups I went there with didn't like enchanters charming.  They felt the risk outweighed the benefit.  Keep in mind that this is unnerfed charm damage in a PoP zone, not nerfed charm damage in an Omens zone.
<br />

<br />
LDoN Normal - The only place I have done a significant amount of charming in groups, mostly because level 65's felt comfortable enough with the easiness of the adventures that the benefit of charming was worth the risk.  Pets are manageable with Word of Morell and hasted Command of Druzzil, but it is still possible to die because of player inattention (the healer snoozes or some goober breaks mez during a bad charm break).
<br />

<br />
LDoN Hard - I would love to try charming here, but I haven't.  Groups I was doing LDoN Hards with didn't even feel comfortable enough to pull more than one or two adds to camp, let alone let me charm.
<br />

<br />
Vxed/Tipt - Ironically, people were asking me to charm here, only because the benefit of having a 1282-quadding pet still outweighed the substantial risks associated with keeping such a pet.  Here is where I felt the risk vs. reward was broken in the "reward" section.  Monsters were dying so quickly that I could not even slow them with Forlorn Deeds before they were dead most of the time.
<br />

<br />
I have never completed Vxed or Tipt successfully, because eventually the group would wipe out because of a bad charm break.  That's called risk, SOE.  If you go to Vxed and Tipt expecting to complete a trial by charming, you have to be very lucky.  If you go there just wanting great XP, charming is desirable.
<br />

<br />
Tactics - I am flagged here but have only been there once or twice for any significant period of time.  People still raid RZ/TZ/VZ often enough on my server where I can't really reliably expect to solo or group here without being interrupted by such a raid.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=824212" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Provender</a>, High Elf Coercer (retired)
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">E67.154/TT h+ 2.9khp 4.8km ft12 !G&gt;&lt;3 e++(+++) o++ T+++ L++ H++(+++) f- g+ b- c++(+++) t+ D- !X</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
