                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">NewarXev says just about it all for me...
<br />

<br />
Charm was never over powered, it took players years to get to the level where charming in PoP/GoD was just common place because people worked at their class.
<br />

<br />
It's taken me two years to get my Enchanter to what it is today and I was just on the verge of breaking into GoD and putting the skills I have learnt to use there.
<br />

<br />
Now I'm told we are too over powered and charm was never meant to be like this? The developers were wrong to look at the Enchanter class and think "they are too powerful" without considering the effort that has to go into getting to that point, which seems to be the case. If not where was the discussion? Where is the information on the new changes being made? Where is our customer service?
<br />

<br />
I don't have 8K HP or 7K Mana but to those Enchanters that have, good for them they deserve it, they deserve the rewards, they deserve some respect from the developers for that achievement alone. We all do.
<br />

<br />
Fact: Charming is not easy unless you work at it!
<br />

<br />
Question: If charming is so overpowered why are there not groups of 6 enchanters running all over the zones killing everything in sight? <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I used to play EQ because I aspired to improve my character. Now I don't see the point. I've been slapped in the face for all my hard work.
<br />

<br />
I'm finding it harder and harder to play my Enchanter and play Everquest and like many others I know will await the release of WoW.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=974389" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.grantnaylor.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/eny.gif" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
