<br />
You don't believe I charm non-equiped LDoN hard mobs with no help?  (well, I need a heal sometimes)
<br />

<br />
Their DPS is only a bit higher than LDoN easy mobs DWing+Hasted.
<br />

<br />
You don't believe my first LDoN hard victory was with a DWing spell+item hasted pet?
<br />

<br />
I stayed back, we had a .. I think it was a bard .. chain casting mez on the pet.  Charm broke, pet was mezzed 0 to 3 seconds later.  I tashed and recharmed.  Bards (and bard-bots) can <span style="font-weight: bold">completely</span> nullify charm break risk, moreso than snare, which is why the DPS reward of charm should not be allowed to diverge from player DPS.  At the same time, if DPS of a pet that doesn't diverge from player DPS, one shouldn't require a bard/snare bot to survive it.  =p
<br />

<br />
The pet didn't solo the LDoN hard.  We had a tank -- charm tanking isn't reliable enough.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The technique is solid though.  Don't bother with haste unless you have good gear, a good healer and you aren't pulling as well.  I generally don't need anyone else to help with CC, but I think that's mostly due to having WoM and Mez Mastery.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
